 Edwin Kiagbodo Clark  The Policemen arrived the Asokoro residence of Chief Clark at 1.30pm left the premises 2.30pm. They searched all the rooms of the Elder statesman, alleging that they were in the house to search for arms which they accused him of keeping. However, they did not find any incriminating evidence or ammunition in the house. According to the Policemen, they stormed the house on the orders of the Inspector- General of Police, Ibrahim Idris. Details later. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .